#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/sun.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "日光"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/sun.rst:6
msgid ""
"A *Sun* lamp provides light of constant intensity emitted in a single "
"direction from very far away. A *Sun* lamp can be very handy for a "
"uniform clear daylight open-space illumination. In the 3D View, the "
"*Sun* light is represented by an encircled black dot with rays emitting "
"from it, plus a dashed line indicating the direction of the light."
msgstr ""
"*Sun（日光）* 灯可以从很远的地方向单一方向发出恒定强度的光。 *Sun*  灯可"
"以非常方便地用于均匀清晰的阳光开放空间照明。在3D视图中，*Sun* 光由带有光"
"线的环绕的黑点表示，再加上一条虚线指示光的方向。"

#: ../../manual/render/lighting/lamps/sun.rst:14
msgid ""
"This direction can be changed by rotating the *Sun* lamp, like any other "
"object, but because the light is emitted in a constant direction, the "
"location of a *Sun* lamp does not affect the rendered result."
msgstr ""
"与其他任何物体一样，可以通过旋转 *日光* 灯来更改此方向，但由于灯光以恒定"
"的方向发射，因此 *日光* 灯的位置不会影响渲染结果。"

